# Steps to install Sass inside my project file:To install Sass, I followed steps used for node.js 

Install Sass Using npm (Node.js Package Manager)
This method works on all platforms (Windows, macOS, Linux).


**Install Node.js:**

     Download and install Node.js from nodejs.org.

**Install Sass:**

Open your terminal or command prompt.
Run the following command to install Sass globally:

    npm install -g sass

**Verify Installation:**

Check the installed version of Sass to ensure it's installed correctly:

    sass --version